Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/contact-point/addressLine2
Object: The second line of a postal address.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/contact-point/hasPostalAddress
Object: Relates a contact point to its postal address.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/contact-point/phoneNumber
Object: Contact point has a phone number.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/contact-point/ContactPoint
Object: A postal address or other contact details.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/contact-point/addressLine5
Object: The fifth line of a postal address.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/contact-point/ContactableThing
Object: A thing that can be contacted. Might be a person or a person in the context of a role or a group.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/contact-point/
Object: Contact point ontology for UK Parliament

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/contact-point/email
Object: Contact point has an email address.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/contact-point/availabilityNote
Object: Temporal availability note for a contact point. Used for constituency office opening days and hours.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/contact-point/addressLine3
Object: The third line of a postal address.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/contact-point/contactForm
Object: URL for a contact form for contacting a contact point. Instead of an email address e.g. some government departments publish a contact form rather than exposing email addresses.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/contact-point/addressLine1
Object: The first line of a postal address.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/contact-point/hasContactPoint
Object: Relates a contactable thing (a person, group or position etc) to a contact point.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/contact-point/addressLine4
Object: The fourth line of a postal address.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/contact-point/faxNumber
Object: Contact point has a fax number.
